item.title: Those lines that inspire
item.description: of all the gin joints in all the towns in all the world, she walks into mine… Nothing really matters, unless you want it to. We are not now that strength which in old days Moved earth and heaven, that which we are, we are, One equal temper of heroic hearts, Made weak by time and fate, but strong in will To strive, to seek, to find, and not to yield.
